Butterfly tenderloins by cutting each tenderloin lengthwise, being careful not to cut through opposite side. Between two sheets of wax paper gently flatten the butterflied tenderloin using the smooth side of a meat tenderizer. In a self-closing plastic bag, combine oil, juice, onion, curry, rind, garlic powder, salt, cumin, cinnamon, pepper and tenderloins. Close bag and refrigerate 1 to 2 hours. On an outdoor charcoal grill, cook tenderloins 5 to 6 minutes per side.